Neural Network¶

In [21]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical

# Assuming you have loaded your data into DataFrame 'df'

# Convert the species column to categorical codes
df['species'] = pd.Categorical(df.species)
df['species'] = df.species.cat.codes

# Convert the response variable to one-hot encoded format
y = to_categorical(df['species'])

# Separate input features (X) and target variable (y)
X = df.drop('species', axis=1).values

# Split the data into training and test sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.30, stratify=y, random_state=123)

# Build the neural network model
model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(100, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train.shape[1],)))  # Use X_train.shape[1] as the input shape
model.add(Dense(3, activation='softmax'))

# Compile the model
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Train the model
history=model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=45, validation_data=(X_test, y_test))
